cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.SY

Reasoning: The paper deals with the semantics of sequential circuits using topos theory, which is a branch of mathematical logic. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also touches upon the theory of presheaves, which is a topic in category theory, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the compilation of a circuit programming language, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of time-sensitive gates and the equational theory of traced categories suggest cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with signal processing, which is a topic in cs.SY (Systems and Control).
